=========================
 BuffClip - TODO
=========================

[HIGH PRIORITY]

[ ] Implement native X11 clipboard owner
    - Remove xclip dependency entirely
    - Read  -> Native X11
    - Write -> Native X11
    - Eliminate Thread.Sleep(20)
    - Support holding F2/F4 for repeated paste

[ ] Windows support
    - WinAPI Clipboard
    - WinAPI global hotkeys
    - Share BufferManager and NetworkManager between Linux/Windows

[ ] Local mode
    - buffclip local
    - Disable all networking
    - Local clipboard manager only

[ ] Automatic reconnect
    - Client retries connection every X seconds
    - Automatically perform FullSync after reconnect

[ ] Security prompt
    - Warn before listening on 0.0.0.0
    - Example:
        "Are you sure you want to expose BuffClip on all interfaces?"
        "Is this your trusted home network? [y/N]"

--------------------------------------------------

[MEDIUM PRIORITY]

[ ] TLS encryption
    - Replace raw NetworkStream with SslStream
    - Encrypt clipboard contents in transit
    - Protect integrity of packets

[ ] Logging
    - INFO
    - WARNING
    - ERROR
    - Optional verbose mode

[ ] Configuration file
    Example:

        listen = 0.0.0.0
        port = 4443
        buffers = 2

        copy_buffer0 = F1
        paste_buffer0 = F2
        copy_buffer1 = F3
        paste_buffer1 = F4

[ ] Command line improvements
    - buffclip server
    - buffclip client <ip>
    - buffclip local

--------------------------------------------------

[NICE TO HAVE]

[ ] Clipboard history
    - Keep previous clipboard entries
    - Navigate history
    - Optional history size

[ ] Clipboard ring
    - Multiple clipboard entries per buffer
    - Quick selector

[ ] Clipboard images
    - Synchronize copied images

[ ] File clipboard support
    - Copy/paste files between machines

[ ] Automatic server discovery
    - mDNS / Zeroconf
    - Connect without typing IP

[ ] Compression
    - Compress large clipboard payloads
    - LZ4 or similar

[ ] CLI status command

    buffclip status

    Connected : Yes
    Server    : 192.168.x.x
    Buffers   : 2
    Latency   : 2 ms

